-- BP Is Said to Approve Plan to Replace Hayward With Dudley in Wake of Spill
-- Stanley Reed
-- 2010-07-26T21:14:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/bp-is-said-to-approve-plan-to-replace-hayward-with-dudley-in-wake-of-spill.html

          
          
             The board of BP Plc as expected
approved a plan to name Robert Dudley as the companyâ€™s new chief
executive officer, replacing Tony Hayward after the company
caused the biggest oil spill in U.S. history, two people
familiar with the situation said.  
